PROOFAGE: Proof of age eligibility requirement for vaccination

LIFTINIT2: Lift second freeze of eviction initiation
COURTCLOSE2: Second suspension of court hearings for evictions

LIFTENF2: Lift second freeze of eviction enforcement
SNAPALLO: SNAP Waiver - Emergency Allotments to Current SNAP Households

SNAPEBT21: SNAP Waiver - Pandemic EBT during school year 2020-2021

MED1135W: Modify Medicaid requirements with 1135 waivers (date of CMS approval)
ACAENROL: Reopened ACA enrollment using a special enrollment period
CHIPLKOT: State had CHIP premium non-payment lock-out period as of January 2019
VISITPER: Stopped personal visitation in state prisons
VISITATT: Stopped in-person attorney visits in state prisons
VISITRES: Began to resume visitation in state prisons
NOCOPAY: Does not charge copays for incarcerated individuals
NOPAYCOV: Waived COVID/respiratory illness-related copays during pandemic for incarcerated individuals
NOPAYALL: Waived all copays during pandemic for incarcerated individuals
YESCOPAY: Did not waive copays for incarcerated individuals
ELECNOSTART: No order to suspend elective medical procedures but did release guidance or orders to resume
WTPRD: No state unemployment waiting period prior to pandemic; or date waiting period waived not found
WV_WTPRD: Waived one week waiting period for unemployment insurance
REI_WTPRD: Reinstated one week waiting period for unemployment insurance
WV_WKSR: Waive work search requirement for unemployment insurance
REI_WKSR: Reinstated work search requirement for UI
UIQUAR: Expand eligibility of unemployment insurance to anyone who is quarantined and/or taking care of someone who is quarantined
UIHIRISK: Expand eligibility to high-risk individuals in preventative quarantine
UICLDCR: Expand eligibility of unemployment insurance to those who have lost childcare/school closures
UIEXTND: Extend the amount of time an individual can be on unemployment insurance
UIMAXEXT: Weekly unemployment insurance maximum amount with extra stimulus (through July 31, 2020) (dollars)
UIMAXCAR: Unemployment insurance maximum duration with Pandemic Emergency Unemployment Compensation CARES extension (weeks)
TUR: Total Unemployment Rate at Extended Benefits program shutoff
TURPRIOR: Total Unemployment Rate relative to prior year (%)
TURPRIOR2: Total Unemployment Rate relative to second prior year (%)
UIMINBP: Minimum total earnings required in the base period to qualify for UI
UIQTRNEED: Number of calendar quarters with earnings in the base period needed to qualify for UI
UIOUTHQBP: Minimum total earnings required outside the highest earning calendar quarter of the base period to qualify for UI
UIREQBPL2Q: Require earnings in the last two calendar quarters of the base period in order to qualify for UI
UIBPEARN300: Earnings in base period required to receive a $300 weekly benefit amount for UI
LMABRN: Made Effort to Limit Abortion Access
TLHlBUPR: Use of telemedicine/telephone evaluations to initiate buprenorphine prescribing
EXTOPFL: Patients can receive 14-28 take-home doses of opioid medication
HMDLVOP: Home delivery of take-home medication by opioid treatment programs
TLHLCL24: Use of telemedicine for schedule II-V prescriptions
WVDEAREQ: Waive requirement to obtain separate DEA registration to dispense outside home state
POV18: Percent living under the federal poverty line (2018)
RISKCOV: Percent at risk for serious illness due to COVID
MH19: Mental health professionals per 100,000 population in 2019
CASSTATE: Were there casino(s) in State? (Land and Non-Land based)
AIANRESN: State has at least one Indian/Alaska Native reservation
VBMEXC: COVID-19 is not an acceptable reason to request application for mail-in ballot unless sick or exposed (as of September 16, 2020)
VBMSIG: Witness or notary signature required for mail-in ballot (as of September 1, 2020)
VBMAUTOBAL: Automatic mail-in ballot system in response to COVID-19 (0,1,2 2 being conditional- see notes for details)
VBMAUTOAP: Automatic applications sent for mail-in ballots in response to COVID-19 (0,1,2 2 being conditional- see notes for details)
VBMGENELEC: Last date of receipt of mail-in ballot request for the general election (by mail or online)
SMALLBUSMINWAGE: Different Minimum Wage for Smaller Businesses
